news.title: Home sales in Toronto rebound 10% in January 2025
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales rose 10% on a month-over-month basis in January to 5,971 units after tumbling 18.2% in December. Compared to January of 2024, sales were down 10.7%.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance's net profit rises 17.17% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Aadhar Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 797.64 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 18.51 per cent from Rs 673.08 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit dips 59.73% in Q3 FY25
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,505.87 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 12.43 per cent from Rs 1,719.54 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Karnataka opens 109 sectors for private investment under new PPP policy
news.para: Grappling with a finance crunch, especially with regard to its guarantee schemes, the govt aims to encourage private investments in sectors ranging from agriculture, energy, healthcare, transportation, and tourism to urban infrastructure, education, and housing.

news.title: Sobha's net profit increases by 43.77% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Sobha's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,256.87 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 76.10 per cent from Rs 713.74 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: With GIS & projects in pipeline, Madhya Pradesh aims to be India’s next IT, tech hub: CM
news.para: Yadav said that the state already has 15 IT parks and 5 IT Special Economic Zones (SEZs). Several new projects are in the pipeline, including Crystal IT Park 3 and 4 in Indore, a 50-acre Data Center Park, and a 1 lakh sq ft IT Tower in Jabalpur.

news.title: Somany Ceramics' net profit declines 58.68% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Somany Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 646.68 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 5.16 per cent from Rs 614.95 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Realty sector seeks interest rate cut to drive housing demand
news.para: "A reduction of 25-30 basis points could signal a supportive stance by the RBI, not only energising the real estate market but also benefiting allied industries such as construction, cement, and steel," NAREDCO President G Hari Babu said.

news.title: Vasai Virar civic body urges residents of 41 illegal buildings to apply for 'proof of residence' certificate
news.para: The corporation urged the residents of the 41 illegal buildings to submit their applications and documents at the earliest to obtain the certificate.

news.title: Vadodara civic body decide on penal action against engineer for housing draw irregularities
news.para: Executive engineer Pramod Vasava of the affordable housing cell of VMC was accused of making changes to the list for the draw for 382 affordable housing units conducted on Aug 7, 2021.

news.title: Jaipur development body extends application time for two residential schemes
news.para: "We received more than one lakh applications for these two schemes, of which the maximum applications came from general category. There are a total of 756 plots for our three upcoming residential schemes, including the one at Patel Nagar," said a JDA official.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body converts 580 residential plots into freehold
news.para: BDA has completed the registration of 580 conveyance deeds from a total of 867 applications, with 462 submissions received through its online portal.

news.title: CLSA upgrades DLF to high conviction outperform, stock rises 4%
news.para: Global brokerage CLSA upgraded DLF to ‘High Conviction Outperform’ with a target of Rs 975, citing compelling valuation and strong growth prospects. Despite rate-sensitive realty stocks trading weak, DLF surged 3.75% to Rs 792.15. CLSA highlights presales growth, new launches, strong balance sheet, and rental income as key positives.

news.title: Guwahati civic body launches special drive to process building permissions
news.para: GMC mayor Mrigen Sarania said this initiative seeks to address the difficulties faced by builders and allottees in securing timely authorisations and certificates, while also tackling outstanding building-related matters.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes eight illegal buildings
news.para: Action was taken against the buildings as the owners were constructing them without getting a building plan approved from the civic body.

news.title: Plan to raise Rs 16,000 crore from sale of MTNL, BSNL assets in last lap
news.para: MTNL and BSNL have more than 600 land parcels and buildings across India, including prime locations in Mumbai, Delhi and Chennai.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to run deficit of Rs 4.5 crore in FY25
news.para: ​From generating a surplus of Rs 25 crore in FY 2022-23, the CHB is heading to run a deficit of around Rs 4.5 crore in FY 2024-25. In the previous year, FY 2023-24, CHB generated a surplus of Rs 17.4 crore.

news.title: Bihar government to provide houses to all in urban areas by August 2025
news.para: According to the official data shared by the office of the chief secretary, the construction of a total of 264,604 houses under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana-Shahri is underway.

news.title: Maharashtra to publish draft RR rates online for public feedback & to ensure transparency
news.para: Ready Reckoner rates serve as govt's assessment of property values and form the basis for stamp duty and registration charges. They typically see limited stakeholder consultation and are implemented every year on April 1.

news.title: Amgen leases five lakh sq ft space in Hyderabad for global capability centre
news.para: Amgen India's technology and innovation centre is located in the RMZ Nexity and Spire Tower in HITEC City. The company is a subsidiary of California-headquartered Amgen Inc.
